message: Look no one wrote about where he lives. He lives in los angeles.
It can just be hollywood debut.
He is not Japanese, he is 100% Burmese. He is just a Japanese signed singer and also a J-pop idol.
Just because her father is Dutch-Canadian does not mean she is Dutch either. She is only Canadian-Korean.
He has never starred in a Taiwanese movie.
Even though there was an episode where it showed Kim going to Africa, it never really showed Ricky going to Namibia. Look I know because I watch these shows all the time. Since we are koreans also.
He is does not have that much fans in Japan.
His father was not British. He was Irish. He once explained on KBS show one time. Seriously, stop giving people false information.

Ok I made some changes to this as well. We all know that he spent his elementary years in Canada. Dont just say Regina,Saskachewan, because there might be a few people that might not know where it is. Just keep it simple. Also, we know that he lived in Michigan. No need to give every detail about his childhood locations. He was born in Seoul, but moved to Canada in 1988, then to Michigan where he attended Troy high school. Also stop repeating Kalamazoo college again and again. We know that guys!
We know that he attended college at Dukes and the UNC school of medicine. It says in the education part. No need to mention his college like a million times.

Ok first off, we all know that Ken jeong was born in Detroit Michigan by reading off his knowledge panel. Also, he was raised in Greensboro, North Carolina. Thats true, but we dont need to include every detail about him or his parents. If you want to give details about his parents, you should make a wikipedia page for his parents as well. This is just about him, not his parents. Its ok to mention his parent's names. But no need to include every detail about them. We all know that people!!
This is too much personal. No need to mention the nationalities of his parents, and his father is American, not British.

Ok in the beginning sentence of the personal life section, it is said that Daniel Kim spends his time between Los Angeles and New York. Then why does it say that he lives in Hawaii. If that was true, it should have said: Daniel splits his time between New York,Los Angeles, and Hawaii.
This is just a typo link. It was not meant to be there. You guys should literally read it first.

In this one, Shannon Kook is fully South African. He is not Canadian. When you read the wiki about him, it says that he moved to Canada to attend a school. Just because he attended school there does not mean that he has Canadian citizenship. Like stop giving in false information.

Ok, first off. Ricky Kim did have parents who live in Hawaii. But that does not mean he lived there. He only visited his parents there. He never resided there. According to KBS interview, he stated that he never resided there, but has visited there frequently due to his parents that resided in Hawaii. He basically spent his entire life in the state of Kansas.
